CIDR:
 -Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (Amazon VPC) is a secure, isolated virtual network.
 - It's allows organizations to host their Amazon Web Services (AWS) resources. 
 - You can now use Amazon VPC IP Address Manager (IPAM) to allocate contiguous IPv6 Classless Inter-Domain Routing (CIDR) blocks).

How CIDR works.
 - go to VPC -> subnet -> ask for CIDR range.
 - 24 is the number ip in a particuar Sbunet
 - 172.16.0.0 --- 172.16.255.255 = 65k ip's
 - -------- | -------- | -------- | --------
 - 8bits      8bits.     8bits.     8bits
 - 0-255.   | 0-255.   | 0-255.   | 0-255
 - we need 256 ip address for finance subnet.
 - total bits = 8*4 = 32 bits
 - first 3 bytes is common. 
 - last byte is lie between 0 --- to --- 255
 - last 8 bit will change can give 256 new ip address for finance subnet
 - so why 172.16.0.0 / 24
 - so, why 24, because we cancel or common first 3 bytes.
 - -------- | -------- | -------- | --------
 - 8bits      8bits.     8bits.     8bits
 - common.    common.    common.    0. -- to -- 255
 - which is 1 byte = 8bit's
 - so, 8bit's * 3 = 24 bit's cancel or common for 256 new ip address.
 - 172.16.0.0 -> 172.16.0.1 -> 172.16.0.2 -> 172.16.0.3 ------- to ----- 172.16.0.254, 172.16.0.255
 - first 3 bytes is common.
 - 172.16.0.0 / 24
 - 32-24 ===> 2^(32-24) ===> 2^8 = 256 ip addresses.
 - this is called CIDR range.
 

Now we want only 2 ip addresses for payment subnet.
 - satrting ip range is 172.16.3.0
 - -------- | -------- | -------- | --------
 - total 32 bit's
 - every bit is represented in 2^.
 - if we write 172.16.3.0/31
 - so we cancelled 31 bit's or hyphen(-)
 - so we have only last bit left which change.
 - 32-31 ==> 2^(32 - 31) = 2^1 = we got 2 ip addresses


